craterdog.collections.interfaces

Interface Dynamic<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - The type of element managed by the collection.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Bag, Dictionary, List, Map, OpenCollection, OrderedCollection, Set, SortableCollection

    public interface Dynamic<E>
    This interface defines the methods that must be implemented by each collection that allows direct access to its elements.
    Author:
    Derk Norton

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean addElement(E element)
      This method adds a new element to the collection.
      int addElements(E[] elements)

    • Method Detail

      • addElement

        boolean addElement(E element)
        This method adds a new element to the collection. If the collection is empty then the new element will be the first element in the collection.
        Parameters:
        element - The new element to be added.
        Returns:
        Whether or not the element was actually added to the collection.

      • addElements

        int addElements(E[] elements)
        This method adds an array of new elements to the collection. The new elements will be added in the order they appear in the specified array.
        Parameters:
        elements - The array of new elements to be added.
        Returns:
        The number of elements that were actually added to the collection.

      • addElements

        int addElements(java.lang.Iterable<? extends E> elements)
        This method adds a list of new elements to the collection. The new elements will be added in the order they appear in the specified collection.
        Parameters:
        elements - The list of new elements to be added.
        Returns:
        The number of elements that were actually added to the collection.

      • removeElement

        boolean removeElement(E element)
        This method removes the specified element from the collection. If the element is not found in the collection, no changes are made.
        Parameters:
        element - The element to be removed.
        Returns:
        Whether or not the element was found.

      • removeElements

        int removeElements(E[] elements)
        This method removes the elements in the specified array from the collection. The number of matching elements is returned.
        Parameters:
        elements - The array of elements to be removed from the collection.
        Returns:
        The number of elements that were actually removed.

      • removeElements

        int removeElements(java.lang.Iterable<? extends E> elements)
        This method removes the specified elements from the collection. The number of matching elements is returned.
        Parameters:
        elements - The list of elements to be removed from the collection.
        Returns:
        The number of elements that were actually removed.
